quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  111,1,"Destroyed were the hands of Abu Lahab, and he lay utterly doomed.",footnotes:182880:1
  111,2,"His wealth did not avail him, nor his acquisitions.",footnotes:182881:1
  111,3,"Surely, he will be cast into a Flaming Fire"
  111,4,"along with his wife, that carrier of slanderous tales;",footnotes:182882:1|182883:2
  111,5,"upon her neck shall be a rope of palm-fibre.",footnotes:182884:1
